0:25:52',' ','','','publish','closed','','','89','','','2015-10-12 10:32:33','2015-10-12 10:32:33','',0,'http://laowainews.com/?p=89',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(92,1,'2015-10-12 16:27:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong>Personal transportation in China </strong>\n\nLiving in a big city has many disadvantages. One of the biggest is that every you want to go will be f-word far.\n\nMetro is a good solution but for small or sometimes even mid-distances may prove to be terribly inefficient. Busses generally are so slow that it doesn\'t even make sense to use them.\n\nImagine the scenario : you live approx 1km from the metro station and the place you work is about 5 kms from where you live. On the metro you need to change 3 times and then from the metro you need to go another 500 ms to get there. It will certainly make you think of some other way of getting to work.\n\nLets get us get a bike\n\n<strong>Bicycle</strong>\n\nAny bike will do. Whenever using anything else than a bike I was asking myself couldn\'t I just bike there?\n\nAdvantages\n\nCheap, relatively fast, uses muscles so no gym, easy to get, popular\n\n&nbsp;\n\nDisadvantages\n\nNot always so fast, uses your muscles, not good for lazy people and not so good on a winter morning\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Ebikes</strong>\n\nMy favorite pick. If you want to buy one what you will usually need is 40-50km distance on one charge (the more the better), 40-50 kmph max. speed and if you don\'t have a good place to hide/park it, it will be actually better if it doesn\'t look good so that nobody will steal it from you. Pedals (moped style!) would be also nice so that you don\'t have to push it when the battery goes flat and a removable battery wouldn\'t be bad especially if you live on the 3rd floor or higher and there is no way to charge it downstairs.\n\nWhile living in Beijing I tried 4 different ebikes and a bicycle and I would say that if you really want to an e-bike a medium-size scooter should be your usual choice. It\'s also best to buy it on Taobao since all these small shops will just take their commission for nothing. Scooters are more universal - you can take something with you like groceries or even things while moving to a new apartment, it\'s more stable to ride than smaller e-bikes and it will normally have factory made rear lights, mirrors, speed meter .which smaller (especially mopeds) don\'t have.\n\nAlso a lead-acid battery will be as heavy as a child elephant so carrying it to your apartment on the 8th floor when the elevator is broken may be a bit difficult\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAdvantages\n\nMuch cheaper than a car or motorcycle or sometimes even not much more expensive than a bike. Fast, Cheap to use, Efficient , Environmentally friendly (if you care - I don\'t),\n\nDisadvantages\n\nQuite dangerous to drive especially without previous experience, really easy to be stolen especially if it looks nice, basically the battery is more important than the bike itself.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>New ways to get by</strong>\n\nA-bike ( A foldable bike)\n\nQuite an interesting invention are A-bikes which are allegedly well adjusted to their function version of foldable bikes. You can take it everywhere you want since it weight just 6-8 kg at least theoretically. Even though the reviews weren\'t so good I tried it out myself\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\n\nFaster than walking, relatively cheap, relatively light, you can take it everywhere with you\n\n<strong>Disadvantages</strong>\n\nNot too much faster than walking, difficult to ride, not really as light as it should.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Electric unicycle</strong>\n\nUnicycle is actually quite convenient for metro commuting. It\'s a wheel that you stand on and that moves itself.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nA picture of my unicycle, the red cable isn\'t a total coincidence - that\'s what happened after a few \"kick-flips\". In general really breakable.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\n\nSurprisingly fun to ride, relatively cheap, relatively fast, fancy, small\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Disadvantages</strong>\n\nActually heavy given that you need to carry it in the metro , difficult to learn how to ride it, easily breakable\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThere is a few other similar vehicles\n\nI found two especially interesting\n\n1:Smartphone skates you just put on your shouse and control with the smartphone. Never seen anybody with it but might be a good idea to try.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n2.Riding pad\n\nNot popular but probably similar to unicycle\n\n&nbsp;','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2015-10-12 16:27:44','2015-10-12 16:27:44','',0,'http://laowainews.com/?p=92',0,'post','',0),(93,1,'2015-10-13 15:56:12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9','Untitled ngg_album','','draft','','','','mixin_nextgen_table_extras','','','2015-10-13 15:56:12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9',0,'http://laowainews.com/?post_type=ngg_album&p=93',0,'ngg_album','',0),(94,1,'2015-10-13 15:56:31','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9','Untitled ngg_album','','draft','','','','mixin_nextgen_table_extras','','','2015-10-13 15:56:31','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9',0,'http://laowainews.com/?post_type=ngg_album&p=94',0,'ngg_album','',0),(95,1,'2015-10-13 16:01:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9','Untitled ngg_album','','draft','','','','mixin_nextgen_table_extras','','','2015-10-13 16:01:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9',0,'http://laowainews.com/?post_type=ngg_album&p=95',0,'ngg_album','',0),(96,1,'2015-10-13 16:19:42','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9','Untitled ngg_album','','draft','closed','','','mixin_nextgen_table_extras','','','2015-10-13 16:19:42','2015-10